@startuml bid-state
title Bid State Diagram

[*] --> PENDING : Buyer submits\nbid amount

PENDING --> VALIDATING : Bidding Service\nreceives bid request

VALIDATING --> REJECTED : Bid amount <\nminimum increment\nOR auction not ACTIVE\nOR buyer already leading

VALIDATING --> CONFLICT_RESOLUTION : Concurrent bid\ndetected on same\nauction row

CONFLICT_RESOLUTION --> ACCEPTED : This bid wins\nconcurrency check\n(highest amount)

CONFLICT_RESOLUTION --> REJECTED : Another bid\nwon concurrency\ncheck

VALIDATING --> ACCEPTED : Bid is valid,\nno conflict

ACCEPTED --> LEADING : Bid persisted,\nauction.currentHighestBid\nupdated\n/ WebSocket broadcast

LEADING --> OUTBID : A higher bid\nis accepted for\nsame auction\n/ send outbid email

LEADING --> WON : Auction ends,\nthis bid is\nhighest\n/ notify winner

LEADING --> LOST : Auction ends,\nreserve not met\n/ notify bidder

OUTBID --> LEADING : Same buyer bids\nagain and leads

OUTBID --> LOST : Auction ends,\nbuyer did not\nretake lead

WON --> [*] : Payment initiated\nfor this bid

LOST --> [*] : Bid archived

REJECTED --> [*] : Rejection logged,\nbuyer notified

note right of CONFLICT_RESOLUTION
  Optimistic locking used.
  Database row version
  checked before commit.
end note

@enduml
